'''April Samuels''' (born April 30),  is an American born rock drummer, [[breast cancer]] survivor, and founder of Breast Cancer Can Stick It! Foundation, Inc. - a 501(c)(3) nonprofit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/allenimage/docs/sept_14/1?e=2927465/9034341|work=Allen Image|title=Dedicated to Beating Breast Cancer|accessdate=September 23, 2015}}</ref>  She is based out of [[Dallas]], Texas. She is best known for her nonprofit and for playing drums as '''Crash Gordon''' in the 80's hair metal cover band, Metal Shop Dallas.  She is also known for co-writing songs for [[Discovery Channel]]'s ''[[Outward Bound]]'' with her bandmates in Frognot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/tv/show/158704/Outward-Bound/credits|work=New York Times|title=Outward Bound|accessdate=May 4, 2014}}</ref>

April Samuels is endorsed by Aquarian Drumheads, Drumtacs, Humes & Berg Drum Cases, Los Cabos Drumsticks, Rockett Drum Works (founded by [[Rikki Rockett]]), Rock-n-Roller Multi-cart [[SABIAN]] Cymbals, and Wornstar Clothing

